  "texts": [
    "• Precision: This metric measures how accurate a model's predictions are by calculating the ratio of true positives to all positive predictions made by the model.",
    "It is often referred to as \"positive predictive value\" and is presented through Eq. 3.",
    "• Specificity: It measures how well a model can correctly identify negative samples.",
    "It is the ratio of true negatives that are correctly identified and presented through Eq. 4.",
    "An ML model with high specificity may have a low false-positive rate, meaning it will rarely incorrectly classify negative examples as positive."
  ],
